                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115 PW/9–2347</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1017</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-09-23">September 23,
                            1947</date>.<lb/>[Received October 3.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Ambassador has the honor to enclose for the information of the Department a
                    copy of a self-explanatory tabulation prepared by the Army Advisory Group which
                    shows the number of Japanese and certain miscellaneous persons repatriated from
                    China since V–J Day.</p>
